1
00:00:39,867 --> 00:00:41,000
<i> Didang, tell me the truth!</i>

2
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:42,867
<i> Are Manuel and Jessica here?</i>

3
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,733
<i> Mom, what's going on here?</i>

4
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:47,600
<i>Are you hiding Manuel
and Jessica here?</i>

5
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:50,033
<i> Sir, Miss Claire told me</i>

6
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:52,567
<i>that my mom didn't come back
here?</i>

7
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:53,867
<i> She didn't come back.</i>

8
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:54,767
<i> Thank you.</i>

9
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,267
<i> They were right!</i>

10
00:00:56,400 --> 00:01:01,067
<i>I'm hiding your dad
without me knowing it!</i>

11
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,533
<i> Ma'am Jessica's here.</i>

12
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:04,300
<i> Thank you, Sir.</i>

13
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:06,300
<i>I'm finally going
to see my daughter.</i>

14
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:07,467
<i> Don't be mad at Coleen.</i>

15
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:08,767
<i> It's not her fault.</i>

16
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:09,900
<i> Shut up, Manuel!</i>

17
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,467
<i> Didang, get him out of here.</i>

18
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,333
<i>I want to spend more time
with Dad.</i>

19
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:15,000
<i> That's why I'm going with him.</i>

20
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:17,533
<i>Hello, my sweet little traitor.</i>

21
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:18,300
<i> Mommy!</i>

22
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,033
<i> Mommy, stop!</i>

23
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,267
<i> Where is your dad?</i>

24
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,767
<i>Hurt me all you want,
but I won't tell you!</i>

25
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:26,300
<i>You're not going to
tell me where he is?</i>

26
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:29,600
<i>Would you really choose
someone you've only known</i>

27
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:30,767
<i> for a few days over us?</i>

28
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:32,100
<i>The ones who've been with you
your whole life?</i>

29
00:01:32,233 --> 00:01:36,833
<i>He filled the void in my heart
that I didn't know I had.</i>

30
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:39,333
<i>Perhaps he caused all that pain.</i>

31
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:41,700
<i>But he's the only one
who can fix it.</i>

32
00:01:41,867 --> 00:01:43,667
<i> I'm giving you permission</i>

33
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,433
<i>to let Manuel and Jessica
stay here.</i>

34
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:48,333
<i>Am I doing the right thing,
Didang?</i>

35
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:49,267
<i> Of course, Ma'am.</i>

36
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,433
<i>You showed them
how kind you are.</i>

37
00:01:52,567 --> 00:01:55,233
<i>Wait, can I use your cellphone?</i>

38
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:56,633
<i>Put it on speaker phone,
sweetie.</i>

39
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:02,900
<i> No!</i>

40
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:04,867
<i> No! Mommy, give it back!</i>

41
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,967
<i> Miss D?</i>

42
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:06,967
<i> Who is this?</i>

43
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,100
<i> Hello, Jessica. Where are you?</i>

44
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:13,667
<i> She's with me.</i>

45
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,733
<i> Hazel!</i>

46
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:16,733
<i>If you want to see
your daughter again,</i>

47
00:02:16,867 --> 00:02:18,133
<i> come over here.</i>

48
00:02:18,267 --> 00:02:19,367
<i> Right now!</i>

49
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:22,500
<i>No, Dad! No matter what happens,
don't come here, Dad!</i>

50
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:23,900
<i> Hazel!</i>

51
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:25,367
<i> No, Mom!</i>

52
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,633
<i> Mom!</i>

53
00:02:26,767 --> 00:02:27,967
<i> Mom!</i>

54
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:33,700
Mom, please,
we have to help them.

55
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:36,533
We can't get involved, sweetie.

56
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:39,533
Just letting them stay here
will cause a lot of trouble.

57
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:41,267
And now you want
to get involved?

58
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,600
What about Jessica?

59
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:46,133
What do you want me to do?

60
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:48,833
We can't get involved
in their family problems.

61
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,600
Mom, we can't let
Hazel hurt Jessica.

62
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:56,633
Coleen, we don't know
the whole story.

63
00:02:56,767 --> 00:03:00,033
We don't know what really
happened to them.

64
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:01,900
Let's not get involved.

65
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:04,733
Mom, please.

66
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:05,467
No!

67
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:10,767
I agreed to let your dad
stay here longer.

68
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,900
It's not part of our deal

69
00:03:13,033 --> 00:03:15,200
to get involved
in their family feud.

70
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,833
Help!

71
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:36,500
Mom! Mom!

72
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:39,233
I'm here, I just got out.

73
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:41,100
I have to get the papers.

74
00:03:41,233 --> 00:03:43,633
Where are you?

75
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:47,633
You're not even here yet,
and you keep rushing me.

76
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:50,400
Can you come pick me up here
instead?

77
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:52,733
I don't want to walk there.

78
00:03:52,867 --> 00:03:54,633
Babe, it's such
nice weather today.

79
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,233
Not too hot, not too cold.

80
00:03:56,367 --> 00:03:57,933
Where are you taking me?

81
00:03:58,067 --> 00:03:59,333
I don't want to ruin
the surprise, okay?

82
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:00,867
Trust me.

83
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,867
You know, I plan this day.

84
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,267
So, I'm sure you're
going to like it.

85
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:10,267
Just wanted to make
your day special, okay?

86
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,233
You're so sweet.

87
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:12,700
You're the sweetest.

88
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:13,700
I swear.

89
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:14,433
Let's go.

90
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,833
What the heck! You're not
watching where you're going.

91
00:04:25,367 --> 00:04:26,800
I'm sorry.

92
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,133
It was an accident.

93
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,433
I'm really sorry.

94
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:37,833
Miss, I'm sorry about that.

95
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,333
That's okay.

96
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:40,633
It was my fault.

97
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,367
I'm really sorry.

98
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,467
- I'm sorry.
- Babe!

99
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,700
- Let's go!
- I'm really, really sory.

100
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:56,700
Oh my...

101
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,567
what are you doing?

102
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,267
What took you so long?
I've been waiting for you

103
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,133
for quite a while now.

104
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,067
I bought something for Tetay.

105
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,933
And you parked too far!

106
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:12,867
There's no parking there.

107
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,233
Why are you mad?

108
00:05:23,267 --> 00:05:24,133
What's with the attitude?

109
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:25,033
Whatever!

110
00:05:25,167 --> 00:05:26,067
Nevermind!

111
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,233
Let's get going.
I want to see my niece.

112
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:29,733
Come on, let's go.

113
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,400
Miss!

114
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:35,633
Miss!

115
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,133
You left something!

116
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:18,533
You were acting
so tough earlier.

117
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:21,067
You were even fighting back.

118
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,833
And now you're crying?

119
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,967
Stop this nonsense and eat.

120
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:34,767
You're not the victim here.

121
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,667
I am.

122
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,033
You even betrayed me.

123
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,300
I did not betray you, Mommy.

124
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,900
You took your dad's side.

125
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,300
Isn't that betrayal
on your part?

126
00:06:46,433 --> 00:06:48,167
No!

127
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,333
I went with him
because he needs help.

128
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,800
Because he is the true
and real victim!

129
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:54,767
Not you! Not me!

130
00:06:56,767 --> 00:06:59,033
So please, Mommy.

131
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:01,267
Mommy, let me go to him.

132
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:10,300
The way you defend your father.

133
00:07:10,433 --> 00:07:13,400
As if you owe him your life.

134
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:14,833
He's my father.

135
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,367
- No.
- Of course, I owe him my life!

136
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,633
No, you don't!

137
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:21,267
And stop arguing with me.

138
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,600
You will never win.

139
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:28,200
You'll never leave this place

140
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,900
until you tell me
where your father is.

141
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:36,533
You can't keep me here
forever, mommy.

142
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:37,767
Let's see about that.

143
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,200
Has Manuel moved into your room?

144
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:59,133
Oh no, he hasn't moved yet.

145
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:02,400
He said he'll wait for Jessica.

146
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:06,433
If her mom let her go.

147
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:12,433
Coleen, how is Jessica doing?

148
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,533
She still hasn't replied.

149
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:20,467
Dad tried to call her
using Didang's phone.

150
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,900
But he can't reach her.

151
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:26,067
Mom.

152
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:28,100
Maybe we should help them.

153
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,300
Take care of this for me,
Didang.

154
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:34,767
Come on, let's go out back.

155
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,000
Okay, I'll take care of this.

156
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:37,967
Why? What's with the backyard?

157
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,933
Why are you startled?

158
00:08:48,067 --> 00:08:49,933
Why does it seem like
you're hiding something?

159
00:09:17,633 --> 00:09:18,967
Hello, bro.

160
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,833
I still can't reach Jessica.

161
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:24,100
Can you please pick me up?

162
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:26,333
<i> Please help me.</i>

163
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:28,767
Bro, you're going to
surrender to Hazel?

164
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,700
You're going back
to your old life?

165
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:31,600
Can you bear that?

166
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:34,533
I have no choice.

167
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:37,200
Hazel might hurt Jessica.

168
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,633
Bro, I really want
to help you out.

169
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:44,033
But I can't because
it's the weekend.

170
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:47,200
We have a scheduled video call
with Mayette.

171
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:50,300
Can you do something
to help me, please?

172
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:52,467
I will tomorrow, I promise.

173
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:55,667
I'll go with you
to get Jessica back.

174
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:06,500
What's with the backyard?

175
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:08,700
Hi! Pretty Mama, Auntie Coleen.

176
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:09,867
- Auntie Didang.
- Tetay!

177
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,967
Oh my, I didn't know you were
here.

178
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,967
Tetay.

179
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,667
I didn't know
she was with you.

180
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,700
Yes, I'm here.

181
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,333
My mom and I just used
the restroom real quick.

182
00:10:17,467 --> 00:10:18,267
Mama, Look!

183
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,167
I got two of these
from the arcade.

184
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,867
This one's for you.

185
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,267
Is this for me?

186
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,400
My granddaughter is so sweet.

187
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:26,700
Thank you, sweetie.

188
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:27,533
Come on, let's go over there.

189
00:10:27,667 --> 00:10:29,067
Let's go.

190
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:29,867
Mom.

191
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:34,400
You didn't answer my question.

192
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,867
What's out back?

193
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:38,767
Coleen?

194
00:10:40,467 --> 00:10:41,333
Didang, what's going on?

195
00:10:44,767 --> 00:10:48,833
Andrea, we thought you
wouldn't be home for a while.

196
00:10:48,967 --> 00:10:53,233
We were planning to surprise you
with a barbecue party.

197
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:54,767
Out there, in our backyard.

198
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:57,100
But you're already here.

199
00:10:57,233 --> 00:10:58,700
Ma'am, I thought we were
going to make adobo?

200
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:02,500
Didang, we're having a barbecue.

201
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:05,100
Oh yeah, we're planning
to have a barbecue.

202
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:06,533
But we should just
make some adobo.

203
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:09,433
It's messy out there.

204
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,267
It's kind of gross.

205
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,033
I want to have a barbecue.

206
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,967
I do, too.

207
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,033
You want to grill with me,
sweetie?

208
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:17,667
Yes, Dad!

209
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:21,067
Okay! Let's go!

210
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,533
Go on.

211
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,800
Miss Felma! Wait for me.

212
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:44,200
Miss Felma!

213
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,667
Before we start
this barbecue party,

214
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,333
we should settle
our differences.

215
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:57,800
Okay?

216
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:58,733
I know we had issues
with each other,

217
00:11:58,867 --> 00:12:00,233
but we can talk about that
tomorrow.

218
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,467
So, Andrea, don't pick
a fight with Coleen.

219
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,600
Why is it always me?

220
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:07,867
I just said nothing
negative today, remember?

221
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,567
Let's all have a good time,
okay?

222
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:10,567
Okay?

223
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:17,533
There!

224
00:12:24,167 --> 00:12:25,567
There, you look like...

225
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:29,100
Hey!

226
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:30,500
I haven't said anything yet!

227
00:12:30,633 --> 00:12:33,567
You never say anything nice!

228
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,233
I haven't said anything yet!

229
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:37,767
<i> Andrea, my Andeng.</i>

230
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,167
Look at what she tried
to do to me, Mom!

231
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,333
My goodness! What are you?
A kid?

232
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:42,867
You made me do it!
You're so annoying!

233
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,700
Look who's the villain now.

234
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:49,300
<i> Felma raised her family well.</i>

235
00:12:49,467 --> 00:12:50,900
<i>I hope they're always like this.</i>

236
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,433
<i> Happy.</i>

237
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,500
<i>I hope they will always
get along.</i>

238
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:57,000
Mom, look!

239
00:12:57,133 --> 00:13:01,933
- You're gonna hurt each other.
- She's trying to burn me!

240
00:13:02,067 --> 00:13:03,033
There.

241
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,267
Jessica.

242
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,300
Get up now.

243
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:30,467
Jessica.

244
00:15:48,967 --> 00:15:49,767
Hey, where's Tetay?

245
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,800
She doesn't feel so good

246
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:54,267
because of what she ate
at the mall.

247
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,233
She said she's going to take
a while,

248
00:15:55,367 --> 00:15:56,933
so we should start without her.

249
00:16:00,567 --> 00:16:02,400
Does she need medicine, sweetie?

250
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:04,100
I already gave her one.

251
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,500
I'll save some food for her.

252
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:06,367
I know her well.

253
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,267
She'll be hungry later.

254
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,433
Her stomach will be empty.

255
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,200
Didang only brought water,
don't we have some juice?

256
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,467
Where is she?

257
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,033
I'll go get some.

258
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:17,300
Let me get it, Mom.

259
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:18,267
I got it.

260
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,833
I also want to check on Tetay.

261
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:22,133
I'll go with you.

262
00:16:22,267 --> 00:16:23,400
I need to use the restroom.

263
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:24,900
Okay, come on.

264
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:31,033
Here, have some water.

265
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:32,067
You can take this.

266
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,300
Give me your cup.

267
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,633
Are you okay?

268
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:47,867
I'm not okay.

269
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,267
I'm not okay, sweetie.

270
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:56,633
It's hard to pretend in
front of your siblings.

271
00:16:56,767 --> 00:16:59,533
I can't keep a secret from them.

272
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:00,767
What secret, Mom?

273
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:05,000
Is this about Coleen's father
again?

274
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,600
No, that's not it, sweetie.

275
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:08,800
Mom, tell me the truth!

276
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:11,533
Don't raise your voice at mom!

277
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:14,300
So what if we're
talking about dad?

278
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:16,400
You don't have concern anyway!

279
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:18,700
So, can you just leave us be?

280
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:19,700
Come on, Mom.

281
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,767
- You're so rude!
- Wait!

282
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:22,600
- Andrea!
- You crossed the line!

283
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:23,400
Coleen!

284
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,033
Coleen, stop.

285
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:30,067
- You two need to stop!
- You're getting on my nerves!

286
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,000
Stop it!

287
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,567
Both of you have to stop this!

288
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,633
Go ahead!

289
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:37,000
You're not going to stop?

290
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:38,667
You really don't want to stop?

291
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,400
Go ahead!

292
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:40,300
Here you go!

293
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:41,733
Kill each other!

294
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:42,467
Here!

295
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:45,733
What's going on, Andrea?

296
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,567
You're blaming me again?

297
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,267
It's always my fault!

298
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,267
Who else should I blame?

299
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,400
I followed you here

300
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:56,333
because I know you're going
to confront Coleen.

301
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:01,100
That's why she's getting bold!

302
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:03,433
Because Mom and Jeffrey's
always taking your side!

303
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:04,633
That's why you're so arrogant!

304
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:07,200
You've got the nerve
to talk back to me!

305
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,267
I'm still your older sister!

306
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,767
I'm older than you!

307
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:11,000
Oh, is that so?

308
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,267
Then act like a sister!

309
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,833
Wow! Listen to that mouth of
yours!

310
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,633
- What's with you?
- That's enough!

311
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:16,567
That's enough!

312
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,200
You, too!

313
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:21,233
Before you stop me and
take this little princess' side,

314
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,033
make sure you know what's really
going on here!

315
00:18:23,167 --> 00:18:25,033
I'm not taking sides, Andrea.

316
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:26,133
Your niece is here.

317
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:29,567
Do you want her to see us
fighting like this?

318
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,933
I know that it's
about her father!

319
00:18:32,067 --> 00:18:33,767
That's right.

320
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:35,833
-They're keeping a secret again!
-Let it go.

321
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:36,667
It's the same thing
over and over again!

322
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,600
I'm getting tired of it.

323
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:41,333
Let's leave them be.

324
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:44,400
There's nothing we
can do about it.

325
00:18:44,533 --> 00:18:46,567
Let's go.

326
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:47,533
Come on.

327
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:53,700
Coleen, why are you talking back
to your sister like that?

328
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,233
You're wrong!

329
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,367
We are!

330
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,867
She started it.

331
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,600
You're disrespecting her.

332
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:05,433
I'm sorry, Mom.

333
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:11,500
Sir Manuel, are you okay?

334
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:13,800
I'm going to go out now,
they might be looking for me.

335
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,067
Okay.

336
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:18,900
How come I always come out
as the villain in this house?

337
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:21,767
<i> Don't carry all the burden.</i>

338
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:24,167
<i>We are both villain
in Coleen's life.</i>

339
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:26,067
That's not true.

340
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:30,633
Sometimes, I feel like
you're taking Coleen's side

341
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,300
when it comes to her dad.

342
00:19:32,433 --> 00:19:34,433
You're wrong.

343
00:19:34,567 --> 00:19:35,533
<i>I'm just trying to
understand her,</i>

344
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,333
<i>the same way I'm trying
to understand you.</i>

345
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:41,033
Andrea, Coleen never got
to experience having a father.

346
00:19:41,167 --> 00:19:42,033
You know, we can't really
blame her

347
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:43,367
if she wants to experience that.

348
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:47,433
Wait.

349
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:48,633
I'm not done yet.

350
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:52,767
I understand where
you're coming from.

351
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:55,300
You get to experience
having a father.

352
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,167
And you got hurt because of him.

353
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,867
<i>Isn't that what you didn't
want Coleen to feel?</i>

354
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:04,200
<i> Because between the two of us,</i>

355
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:08,733
<i>weren't you the one who got hurt
the most when Dad left us?</i>

356
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:10,333
That's not true.

357
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:12,800
It's true.

358
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,933
You love him so much.

359
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:16,633
Aren't you his daddy's girl?

360
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,233
<i> You're his...</i>

361
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:27,133
his Andeng.

362
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:30,900
<i>Mom, Dad promised us that
he would come back home.</i>

363
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:32,900
<i> He will keep his promise.</i>

364
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:35,700
<i>You shouldn't have
argued with him!</i>

365
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,900
<i> Don't blame her!</i>

366
00:20:38,033 --> 00:20:40,167
<i> It's all Dad's fault!</i>

367
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:44,167
<i>Mom, you're his wife,
get him back from that Hazel.</i>

368
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:45,800
<i> That's right, Mom.</i>

369
00:20:45,933 --> 00:20:47,900
<i> Please take Dad back.</i>

370
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:50,000
<i> We can't, sweetie.</i>

371
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:52,700
He's married to her now.

372
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:56,267
<i>But he's married to you,
is that possible?</i>

373
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,233
<i> We're not married.</i>

374
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,467
Dad left us.

375
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:04,533
He left us, Jeffrey.

376
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,367
<i> Dad left us.</i>

377
00:21:09,433 --> 00:21:11,800
He abandoned us, Jeffrey.

378
00:21:15,133 --> 00:21:16,933
<i> It hurts, Jeffrey.</i>

379
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,200
<i> It hurts.</i>

380
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:25,333
It hurts to lose a Dad.

381
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:40,000
It hurts to lose a Dad.

382
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,233
Have some dessert.

383
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,133
Here's some juice.

384
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:15,167
It's really cold.

385
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:16,667
Mom, where's Coleen?

386
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:20,833
She went to her room.

387
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:22,633
She needs to get something.

388
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:25,000
I forgot to get something, too.

389
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:26,367
I forgot the flan.

390
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,200
Wait here, I'll be right back.

391
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,767
Where are you going?

392
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:35,800
You're trying to escape from me?

393
00:23:35,933 --> 00:23:37,567
Mom, let me go!

394
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:45,133
Jessica!

395
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:48,500
Jessica!

396
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:56,467
Why don't you try to
look at Felma's house?

397
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:59,033
Actually, I'm already here.

398
00:23:59,167 --> 00:23:59,967
Then do something.

399
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,200
Please book a cab for me,

400
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:03,300
and help me get out of here,
please.

401
00:24:03,433 --> 00:24:05,900
If you go back to Miss Hazel,

402
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:08,033
she'll take you away
from me again!

403
00:24:08,167 --> 00:24:09,833
We'll get separated again.

404
00:24:09,967 --> 00:24:13,867
Please stop fighting with
each other, Aunt Andrea.

405
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,267
It's bad.

406
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,167
We know that, Tetay.

407
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,100
It's all Coleen's fault.

408
00:24:19,233 --> 00:24:22,267
Is it because she is still
communicating with your dad?

409
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:24,233
Give Aunt Coleen permission.

410
00:24:24,367 --> 00:24:28,367
Once the pain subsides,
you should forgive Grandpa.

411
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:32,433
Here's Miss Felma's
special flan.

412
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:34,300
How come you're the one
who brought that here?

413
00:24:34,433 --> 00:24:35,767
Where's Mom?

414
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:38,200
You want to get away from Hazel,
don't you?

415
00:24:38,333 --> 00:24:40,300
Why are you going back
to her then?

416
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:42,200
She has Jessica.

417
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:44,033
Yes, Dad. I'm here.

418
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:44,967
I escaped Mom.

419
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:46,033
<i> Thank God.</i>

420
00:24:46,167 --> 00:24:46,967
I'm going to look for them.

421
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,000
Where are you going?

422
00:24:48,133 --> 00:24:50,367
I'm going to look
for Mom and Coleen.

423
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:52,600
I'm going to find out what
they're keeping from us.

424
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:54,133
Be careful, Jessica, okay?

425
00:24:54,267 --> 00:24:55,567
<i> Watch out when you come here.</i>

426
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:58,500
<i>Andrea and Jeffrey's
at the pool area.</i>

427
00:24:58,633 --> 00:24:59,733
I know.

428
00:24:59,867 --> 00:25:00,800
I'm hiding right now.

429
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:03,167
Because Jeffrey's here.

430
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:05,767
What? Jessica, be careful,
please.

431
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:07,700
Why are you making me cry?
Come on.

432
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:08,967
Now we're even.

433
00:25:16,267 --> 00:25:16,833
Hey!

434
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:20,200
Who are you?
